<br>
A breakdown of what each piece would cost would be immeasurably helpful, if someone could oblige. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dalninil>Dalninil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 58<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/26/01 7:55:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=80.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The cost of fine platemail?</span><hr size=1> eqtraders... will give you the list of stuff you need.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uladyalmea.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lady Almea</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/26/01 9:52:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=80.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The cost of fine platemail?</span><hr size=1> I do not seek to take up the trade, but rather to buy the end results. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ufalconeroftunare.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Falconer of Tunare</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/27/01 2:39:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=80.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The cost of fine platemail?</span><hr size=1> Fine plate pieces usually sold for around 100pp and upwards, with maybe the low hundreds for the tough bits I think - but it is dependant on the smith.<br>
<br>
As suggested check out Eqtraders - an honest blacksmith will look more favourably on someone who will supply some or all of the components (it is a good idea to collect spiderling silks and low quality skins for fineplate in preparation)<br>
<br>
 <p><center><img src="http://members.aol.com/jimturner99/gyrhawk"></center> <b><center>Gyrhawk - Tunare's Falconer</center></b></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ufalconeroftunare.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Falconer of Tunare</A> at: 12/27/01 2:44:29 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uladyalmea.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lady Almea</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/27/01 7:41:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=80.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The cost of fine platemail?</span><hr size=1> A hundred platinum crowns (or more?) for a fine steel bracer? Sounds a bit much to me, but I'll have to watch the economy in general a bit more closely.<br>
<br>
My thanks, Falconer. While I'd have preferred examples of prices for separate pieces (I'm sure a smith I discuss it with will be more specific if I cannot complete some of my quest armour), this is a great help to me. I'll keep this in mind in the coming weeks. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dalninil>Dalninil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 61<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/28/01 6:31:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=80.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The cost of fine platemail?</span><hr size=1> 100 + isn't a bad price<br>
mold 30 - 50 pp<br>
medium folded sheet 10-30 depending on the peices needed<br>
leather padding <br>
spiderling silks and low quality pelts 10pp<br>
<br>
base cost 50- 80pp * 1.5 for failure rate making it<br>
75-120<br>
<br>
very mind the amount of time and cash it takes to get to that skill level at a huge loss<br>
<br>
profit magrin *2 so 150 to 240 per peice<br>
<br>
best thing to do is pay for combines and buy enough raw material to make 2 or 3 of what you want.<br>
<br>
If you don't beleive me you could go get a list of the stuff you need and price it out this is off my head as well as I'm not smithing on this server.<br>
<br>
 oh it also gives you the places to find the merchants. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/unakath.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nakath</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/28/01 12:18:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=80.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The cost of fine platemail?</span><hr size=1> In a previous incarnation, this is how i calculated cost for fine plate.<br>
<br>
20.5pp/ folded sheet of steel<br>
5pp for the leather backing (mind you, on that server, this was the least I could pay for the damned things if I didn't make them myself)<br>
+cost of mold<br>
+risk of getting mold factor (i was KOS in freeport and neriak, so i either needed a teleport for small molds (before velious and luclin, mind you) to kaladim or I needed to sneak into neriak and buy them (apprehensive to vendor, KOS to everyone else, don't ask me how, i started that way)) usually 5pp per mold surcharge if I had to buy special molds.<br>
<br>
Bracer usually wound up costing 27pp, if i remember correctly.<br>
<br>
Since i was 'skilling up' I just charged 25pp per piece profit and had the buyer pay cost for all attempts. <p>Nakath<BR>
